obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (22973)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Auroville Foundation Act, 1988.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22973&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (22974)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22974&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Auroville" means so much of the undertakings as form part of, or are relatable to, the cultural`
  line `township which is known as Auroville and the charter of which was proclaimed by the 'Mother' on`
  line `the 28th day of February, 1988;`
  line
  line `(c) "Council" means the Auroville International Advisory Council constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) "Custodian" means the person who is appointed as the Custodian under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 7 in respect of the undertakings;`
  line
  line `(e) "Foundation" means the Auroville Foundation established under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) "Governing Board" means the Governing Board of the Foundation constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "Residents Assembly" means the Residents' Assembly of the Foundation;`
  line
  line `(j) "Society" means Sri Aurobindo Society, being a Society as defined in the West Bengal`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1961 (West Bengal Act XXVI of 1961), and having its registered office at`
  line `Calcutta in the State of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(k) "specified date" means such date as the Central Government may, for the purpose of section 9,`
  line `by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(l) "trust" or "body" means a trust or body specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(m) "undertakings" means the undertakings of the Society, trust or body which had vested in the`
  line `Central Government under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (22975)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of certain undertakings of the Society, trust and bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22975&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, so much of the undertakings of the Society, trust and body as`
  line `form part of, or are relatable to Auroville, and the right, title and interest of the Society, trust and body, in`
  line `relation to such undertakings, shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (22976)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22976&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings vested under section 3 shall be deemed to`
  line `include all the assets, rights, leaseholds, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property (movable and`
  line `immovable), including lands, buildings, works, workshops, projects, stores, instruments, machinery,`
  line `automobiles and other vehicles, cash balances, funds, including reserve funds, investments and book`
  line `debts of the Society, trust or body as form part of, or are relatable to, Auroville and all other rights and`
  line `interests arising out of such properties as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership,`
  line `possession, power or control of the Society, trust or body, whether within or without India, and all`
  line `books of account, registers, maps, plans and all other documents of whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties and assets as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 3 shall, by force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage,`
  line `charge, lien and all other incumbrances affecting them or of any attachment, injunction, decree or order of`
  line `any court or other authority restricting the use of such properties or assets in any manner or appointing`
  line `any receiver in respect of the whole or any part of such properties or assets shall be deemed to have been`
  line withdrawn.
  line
  line `(3) Any licence or other instrument granted to the Society, trust or body in relation to any undertaking`
  line `which has vested in the Central Government under section 3 at any time before the appointed day and in`
  line `force immediately before the appointed day, shall continue to be in force on and after such day in`
  line `accordance with its tenor in relation to and for the purposes of such undertaking or where the undertaking`
  line `is directed under section 6 to vest in the Foundation, the Foundation shall be deemed to be substituted in`
  line `such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had been granted to the Foundation`
  line `and the Foundation shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which the Society, trust or body would`
  line `have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding, of whatever nature, in relation to`
  line `any property or asset which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, instituted or preferred`
  line `by or against the Society, trust or body is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any`
  line `way, prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertakings of the Society, trust or body or of`
  line `anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or`
  line `enforced by or against the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Society, trust or body`
  line `are directed under section 6 to vest in the Foundation, by or against the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (22977)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Central Government or Foundation to be liable for certain prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22977&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every liability in`
  line `relation to any undertaking in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be enforceable against`
  line `the Central Government and not against the Society, trust or body, or where the said undertakings are`
  line `directed, under section 6, to vest in the Foundation, against the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (22978)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakings in the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22978&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, the Central Government shall,`
  line `as soon as may be after the appointed day, direct, by notification, that the undertakings and the right, title`
  line `and interest of the Society, trust or body in relation to such undertakings which had vested in the Central`
  line `Government under section 3, shall, instead of continuing to vest in the Central Government, vest in the`
  line `Foundation either on the date of publication of the notification or on such earlier or later date as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the Society, trust or body in relation to the undertakings vest,`
  line `under sub-section (1), in the Foundation, the Foundation shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be`
  line `deemed to have become the owner in relation to such undertakings and the rights and liabilities of the`
  line `Central Government in relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be`
  line `deemed to have become, the rights and liabilities, respectively, of the Foundation.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (22979)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22979&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction, control and`
  line `management of the affairs of the undertakings, the right, title and interest in relation to which have vested`
  line `in the Central Government under section 3, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6, vest in the Foundation; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no such direction has been made by the Central Government, vest in a Custodian`
  line `appointed by the Central Government under sub-section (2),`
  line
  line `and, thereupon, the Foundation, or the Custodian so appointed, as the case may be, shall be entitled to`
  line `exercise all such powers and do all such things as the Society, trust or body, as the case may be, is`
  line `authorised to exercise and do in relation to its undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint any person as the Custodian of the undertakings in relation`
  line `to which no direction has been made by it under sub-section (1) of section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian so appointed shall receive such remuneration as the Central Government may fix`
  line `and shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (22980)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duties of persons in charge of management by undertakings to deliver all assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22980&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the`
  line `vesting of the management of the undertakings in the Foundation or on the appointment of a Custodian`
  line `under section 7, all persons in charge of the management of the undertakings immediately before such`
  line `vesting or appointment shall be bound to deliver to the Foundation or Custodian, as the case may be, all`
  line `assets, books of account, registers and other documents in their custody relating to the undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the Custodian as to the powers and duties of the Custodian and such Custodian may also, if`
  line `it is considered necessary so to do, apply to the Central Government at any time for instructions as to the`
  line `manner in which the management of the undertakings shall be conducted or in relation to any other matter`
  line `arising in the course of such management.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person, who on the appointed day, has in his possession or under his control, any books,`
  line `documents or other papers relating to the undertakings shall be liable to account for the said books,`
  line `documents or other papers to the Central Government or the Foundation, as the case may be, and shall`
  line `deliver them up to the Central Government or the Foundation or to such person or body of persons as the`
  line `Central Government or the Foundation may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the Foundation may take or cause to be taken, all necessary steps for`
  line `securing possession of all undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Foundation`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Society, trust or body shall, within such period as the Central Government may allow in this`
  line `behalf, furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all its properties and assets, as on the`
  line `appointed day pertaining to the undertakings and, for this purpose, the Central Government or the`
  line `Foundation shall afford to the Society, trust or body all reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (22981)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Certain powers of the Central Government or the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22981&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or`
  line `the Foundation shall be entitled to receive up to the specified date, to the exclusion of all other persons,`
  line `any money due to the Society, trust or body in relation to its undertakings which have vested in the`
  line `Central Government or the Foundation, as the case may be, and realised after the appointed day,`
  line `notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (22982)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Establishment and incorporation of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22982&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for the purpose`
  line `of this Act, a Foundation, to be called the Auroville Foundation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Foundation shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Foundation shall consist of the following authorities, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Governing Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the Residents' Assembly;`
  line
  line `(c) the Auroville International Advisory Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (22983)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22983&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) not more than seven members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst`
  line `persons, who have--`
  line
  line `(a) rendered valuable service to Auroville;`
  line
  line `(b) dedicated themselves to the ideals of life-long education, synthesis of material and`
  line `spiritual researches or human unity;`
  line
  line `(c) contributed significantly in activities that are being persued or are envisaged to be`
  line `promoted in Auroville, including activities relating to environment, afforestation, arts and crafts,`
  line `industry, agriculture, humanities, sciences and integral yoga;`
  line
  line `(ii) two representatives of the Central Government to be nominated by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall nominate a Chairman of the Governing Board from amongst the`
  line `members nominated by it under clause (i) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the Foundation shall vest`
  line `in the Governing Board which may exercise all the powers and discharge all the functions which may be`
  line `exercised or discharged by the Foundation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Governing Board may associate with itself in such manner and for such purposes as may be`
  line `prescribed, any persons whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the Governing`
  line `Board relevant to the purposes for which he has been associated, but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(5) No act or proceeding of the Governing Board or any committee appointed by it under section 16`
  line `shall be invalidated merely by reason of,--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Governing Board or such`
  line `committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the nomination of a person acting as a member of the Governing Board or such`
  line `committee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Governing Board or such committee not affecting the`
  line `merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (22984)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Term of office of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22984&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, the term of office of`
  line `the members of the Governing Board including the Chairman shall be four years from the date of their`
  line nomination.
  line
  line `(2) An outgoing member of the Governing Board shall be eligible for re-nomination.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member nominated to fill a casual vacancy in the Governing Board shall`
  line `continue for the remainder of the term of the member in whose place he is nominated.`
  line
  line `(4) A member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government`
  line `but he shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (22985)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Salary and allowances and other conditions of service of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22985&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman of the`
  line `Governing Board shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and such conditions of service in respect`
  line `of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (22986)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Meetings of the Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22986&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall meet at least once a year at`
  line `Auroville at such time as may be fixed by the Chairman of the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All the decisions at any meeting of the Governing Board shall be taken by a majority of the`
  line `members present and voting:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of equality of votes, the Chairman of the Governing Board shall have a`
  line `casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (22987)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Secretary and other officers of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22987&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint a`
  line `Secretary to the Foundation to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the Chairman of the`
  line `Governing Board as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and such conditions of service in`
  line `respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to such control, restrictions and conditions as may be prescribed, the Governing Board`
  line `may appoint such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(4) The Chairman, Secretary and other officers and employees of the Foundation shall not undertake`
  line `any work unconnected with their duties under this Act except with the permission of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (22988)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Committees of the Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22988&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board may appoint such committees`
  line `as may be necessary for the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The Governing Board shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1), such number of persons who are not members of the Governing Board as it may`
  line `think fit, and the persons so co-opted shall have the right to attend the meetings of the committee, and`
  line `take part in the proceedings of the committee, but shall not have the right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (22989)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers and functions of the Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22989&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The powers and functions of the Governing`
  line `Board shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to promote the ideals of Auroville and to coordinate activities and services of Auroville in`
  line `consultation with the Residents Assembly for the purposes of cohesion and integration of Auroville;`
  line
  line `(b) to review the basic policies and the programmes of Auroville and give necessary directions`
  line `for the future development of Auroville;`
  line
  line `(c) to accord approval to the programmes of Auroville drawn up by the Residents' Assembly;`
  line
  line `(d) to monitor and review the activities of Auroville and to secure proper management of the`
  line `properties vested in the Foundation under section 6 and other properties relatable to Auroville;`
  line
  line `(e) to prepare a master-plan of Auroville in consultation with the Residents' Assembly and to`
  line `ensure development of Auroville as so planned;`
  line
  line `(f) to authorise and coordinate fund-raising for Auroville and to secure proper arrangements for`
  line `receipts and disbursement of funds for Auroville.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (22990)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Residents' Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22990&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Residents' Assembly shall consist of all the residents of`
  line `Auroville who are for the time being entered in the register of residents maintained under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary to the Governing Board shall maintain the register of residents in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed and all the persons who are residents of Auroville and who are of the age of eighteen`
  line `years and above are entitled to have their names entered in the register on an application made to the`
  line `Secretary in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) All the names of residents, which have been included in the register maintained by the`
  line `Administrator appointed under section 5 of the Auroville (Emergency Provisions) Act, 1980 (59 of 1980)`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, shall be deemed to have been included in the register maintained`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (22991)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Functions of Residents' Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22991&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Residents Assembly shall perform such functions`
  line `as are required by this Act and shall advise the Governing Board in respect of all activities relating to the`
  line `residents of Auroville.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing powers, the Residents' Assembly may--`
  line
  line `(a) allow the admission or cause the termination of persons in the register of residents in`
  line `accordance with the regulations made under section 32;`
  line
  line `(b) organise various activities relating to Auroville;`
  line
  line `(c) formulate the master plan of Auroville and make necessary recommendations for the`
  line `recognition of organisations engaged in activities relatable to Auroville for the approval of the`
  line `Governing Board;`
  line
  line `(d) recommend proposals for raising funds for Auroville for the approval of the Governing Board.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of carrying of its functions, the Residents' Assembly may establish such`
  line `committees as it may consider necessary which shall represent it in relation to the functions to be`
  line `performed by the Governing Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (22992)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Working Committee or Residents' Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22992&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Working Committee of the`
  line `Residents' Assembly which shall assist the Residents' Assembly or, as the case may be, the Governing`
  line `Board, in discharging its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Working Committee shall consist of not more than seven members to be chosen by the`
  line `Residents' Assembly from among themselves.`
  line
  line `(3) The manner of choosing the members of the Working Committee and their term of office shall be`
  line `such as may be decided by the Residents' Assembly.`
  line
  line `(4) The Working Committee may, with the approval of the Governing Board, create or constitute`
  line `other organisations, trusts, societies or associations relatable to Auroville if the Working Committee is`
  line `satisfied that such organisations, trusts, societies or associations have--`
  line
  line `(a) their headquarters at Auroville;`
  line
  line `(b) declared than in all matters relating to Auroville they shall act in conformity with the`
  line `decisions of the Governing Board and that their main object is to promote the ideals laid down in the`
  line `Charter of Auroville proclaimed by the 'Mother' on the 28th day of February, 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (22993)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22993&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Auroville International Advisory Council shall consist of not more`
  line `than five members nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may nominate the members of the Council from amongst persons who in`
  line `its opinion are devoted to the ideals of human unity, peace and progress.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may, on its own motion or on a reference made to it by the Governing Board, advise`
  line `the Governing Board on any matter relating to the development and management of Auroville.`
  line
  line `(4) In tendering any advice to the Governing Board, the Council shall endeavour to secure that--`
  line
  line `(a) the ideals for which Auroville has been established are encouraged, and`
  line
  line `(b) the residents of Auroville are allowed freedom to grow and develop activities and institutions`
  line `for the fulfilment of the aspirations and programmes envisaged in the said Charter of Auroville.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be a Chairman of the Council who shall be elected by the members of the Council`
  line `from among themselves.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of, the method of filling casual vacancies among, and the allowances and other`
  line `remuneration, if any, payable to, the members of the Council, shall be such as may be determined by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The Council shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (22994)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Dissolution of the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22994&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification and for`
  line `reasons to be specified therein, direct that the Foundation shall be dissolved from such date and for such`
  line `period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Foundation to make representation against the proposed dissolution and shall consider`
  line `the representation, if any, of the Foundation.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Foundation is dissolved under the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members of the Governing Board, notwithstanding that the terms of their office had not`
  line `expired, shall, from the date of dissolution, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Foundation shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised`
  line `and performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all properties vested in the Foundation shall, during the period of dissolution, vest in the`
  line `Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) as soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Foundation shall be reconstituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (22995)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Grant by Central Government to the Foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22995&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the`
  line `Foundation to discharge its functions under this Act, the Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Foundation, in each financial year,`
  line `such sums of money as that Government considers necessary by way of grant, loan or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (22996)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Duty to furnish returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22996&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall furnish to the Central Government`
  line `at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed, or as the Central Government may direct,`
  line `such returns and statements and such particulars as the Central Government may, from time to time,`
  line require.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Governing Board shall, as soon as`
  line `possible after the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form and`
  line `before such date as may be prescribed giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and`
  line `programmes during the previous year.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is`
  line `received before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (22997)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Borrowing powers of the Governing Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22997&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made in this`
  line `behalf, the Governing Board shall have the power to borrow on the security of the properties of Auroville`
  line `or any other asset for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (22998)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22998&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the income and expenditure`
  line `account and the balance-sheet in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Foundation shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenses incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Foundation to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Foundation shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books,`
  line `accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the officer of the`
  line Foundation.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Foundation, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (22999)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=22999&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (23000)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by the foundation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23000&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered`
  line `into by the Society, trust or body in relation to its undertakings for any service, sale or supply, and in`
  line `force immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from the expiry of one hundred and eighty days`
  line `from that day, cease to have effect unless such contract is, before the expiry of the said period, ratified in`
  line `writing by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Foundation, and in ratifying such contract,`
  line `the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Foundation may make such alterations or`
  line `modifications therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Foundation shall not omit to ratify a`
  line `contract and shall not make any alteration or modification therein,--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous or has been entered into in bad faith`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Foundation;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) except after giving the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for its refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (23001)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23001&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `A person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of the undertakings of`
  line `the Society, trust or body, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or, as`
  line `the case may be, the Foundation or any person or body of persons authorised by that Government or`
  line `the Foundation; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `the Society, trust or body or wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or, as the`
  line `case may be, the Foundation or any person or body of persons authorised by that Government or the`
  line `Foundation, any documents relating to such undertakings which may be in his possession, custody or`
  line `control, or fails to deliver to the Central Government or, as the case may be, the Foundation or any person or body of persons authorised by that Government or the Foundation any assets,`
  line `books of account, registers or other documents in his possession, custody or control relating to the`
  line `undertakings of the Society, trust or body; or`
  line
  line `(c) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of the undertakings of the Society,`
  line `trust or body,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (23002)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23002&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the Custodian or any officer or`
  line `other person authorised by that Government or the Foundation for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (23003)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23003&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which and the purpose for which any person may be associated with the`
  line `Governing Board under sub-section (4) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties which the Secretary to the Governing Board may perform under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) the control, restrictions and conditions subject to which the Governing Board may appoint`
  line `officers and employees under sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the register of residents may be maintained under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(e) the time within which and the form and manner in which the Governing Board may furnish`
  line `returns and reports under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and the date before which the Governing Board shall submit reports to the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(g) the rules subject to which the Governing Board shall have the power to borrow under`
  line `section 25;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (23004)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23004&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Board may make regulations, not inconsistent`
  line `with this Act and the rules made thereunder, for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Governing Board or at the meetings of the`
  line `committees appointed by it and the number of members which shall form a quorum at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) the delegation to the Chairman, other members, Secretary or other officers of the Governing`
  line `Board, of any of the powers, duties of the Governing Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and other allowances payable to persons associated under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 11 or co-opted under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) the pay and allowances and leave and other conditions of service of officers (other than those`
  line `appointed by the Central Government) and other employees of the Foundation;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance of the accounts of the Foundation;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Foundation and its various`
  line committees;
  line
  line `(g) the appointment by the Governing Board of agents to discharge on its behalf any of its`
  line functions;
  line
  line `(h) admission or termination of persons in the register of residents.`
  line
  line `(3) No regulation made by the Governing Board shall have effect until it has been approved by the`
  line `Central Government and published in the Official Gazette, and the Central Government, in approving the`
  line `regulation, may make changes therein which appear to it to be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (23005)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23005&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every rule or regulation made under this`
  line `Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions and if before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or both`
  line `Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (23006)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595&sectionId=23006&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00021_198854_1517807325595
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
